section.section:
"Person in interest" means a person who:
Is related by blood or marriage to the person interred in a burial site;
Is a domestic partner, as defined in § 1-101 of the Health - General Article, of a person interred in a burial site;
Has a cultural affiliation with the person interred in a burial site; or
Has an interest in a burial site that the Office of the State's Attorney for the county where the burial site is located recognizes is in the public interest after consultation with a local burial sites advisory board or, if such a board does not exist, the Maryland Historical Trust.
